==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Festive
<hw>Fes"tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>festivus</ets>, fr. <ets>festum</ets> holiday, feast. See
<er>feast</er>, and cf. <er>Festivous</er>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to,
or becoming, a feast; festal; joyous; gay; mirthful; sportive.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Fes"tive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The glad circle round them yield their souls⟦br⟧
To <qex>festive</qex> mirth and wit that knows no gall.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Festivity</ent>⟦br⟧
